HEX alpha kernel 0.0.x (*** See Alpha Kernel Requirements Doc ***)

* - detect CPU attributes [DONE]
*  -detect IO devices [DONE]
* - detect RAM available [DONE]
* - read CMOS [DONE]

* - kernel heap allocation
	- ordered array implementation [DONE]
	- kernel heap implementation [DONE - But needs improvement. VERY primitive implementation]

* - serial port logging functionality [DONE]
	* - allow for logging to a serial port [DONE]

* - set up data structures to store 
		- memory [DONE]
			- start and end address of memory regions
			- size of each region
			- size of high memory (above 1MB)
			- size of low (conventional) memory (0 - 640KB)
		- CPU information
			- processor manufacturer (Intel, AMD,etc..)
			- processor model and family (athlon, pentium, etc...)
			- 32-bit or 64-bit
			- processor features (FPU, Virtual mode, etc..) 

* - design a set of system calls

* - paging support

* - place version info into the kernel binary [DONE - for now version is hard coded]

* - integrate automated unit tests into the build
